				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
					<div class="mv-create-jtr-wrapper"><a href="#mv-creation-13-jtr" class="mv-create-jtr mv-create-jtr-slot-v2 mv-create-jtr-link mv-create-jtr-button-uppercase"><svg class="mv-create-jtr-caret" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1"  viewBox="0 0 444.819 444.819" width="16px" height="16px"><path d="M434.252,114.203l-21.409-21.416c-7.419-7.04-16.084-10.561-25.975-10.561c-10.095,0-18.657,3.521-25.7,10.561 L222.41,231.549L83.653,92.791c-7.042-7.04-15.606-10.561-25.697-10.561c-9.896,0-18.559,3.521-25.979,10.561l-21.128,21.416 C3.615,121.436,0,130.099,0,140.188c0,10.277,3.619,18.842,10.848,25.693l185.864,185.865c6.855,7.23,15.416,10.848,25.697,10.848 c10.088,0,18.75-3.617,25.977-10.848l185.865-185.865c7.043-7.044,10.567-15.608,10.567-25.693 C444.819,130.287,441.295,121.629,434.252,114.203z"/></svg> Jump to Recipe</a></div><style>.mv-create-jtr-wrapper{margin-bottom:20px}a.mv-create-jtr-link{display:inline-block;padding:10px 10px 10px 0;color:#333;font-size:16px;text-decoration:none!important;-webkit-transition:color .5s;transition:color .5s}a.mv-create-jtr-link:hover,a.mv-create-jtr-link:focus{color:#666}.mv-create-jtr-link .mv-create-jtr-caret{margin-right:5px;padding-top:6px;fill:#333}.mv-create-jtr-link:hover .mv-create-jtr-caret,.mv-create-jtr-link:focus .mv-create-jtr-caret{fill:#666}.mv-create-jtr-button-uppercase{text-transform:uppercase}</style>
<p><strong>Baking eggs in a muffin tin</strong> is the easiest way to streamline your <strong>breakfast meal prep</strong>! Once you know <strong>how to bake eggs</strong>, you&#8217;ll be amazed at how easy it is!</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><a href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/257831147405222568/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><img fetchpriority="high" fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="512" height="1024" data-pin-nopin="nopin" data-pin-url="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/?tp_image_id=1701" data-pin-title="How to Bake Eggs in a Muffin Tin in the Oven" data-pin-description="Egg recipes, egg recipes in muffin tins, egg recipes for breakfast, egg recipes healthy, egg recipes for breakfast healthy, egg recipes easy, egg recipes keto, egg recipes low carb, egg recipes make ahead, egg recipes hard boiled, egg recipes for lunch, egg recipes baked, egg recipes for kids, egg recipes quick, egg recipes clean eating, egg recipes creative, egg recipes snacks. #eggs #breakfastrecipes #breakfastmealprep #eggrecipes #bakedeggs #lowcarbbreakfast #ketobreakfast | keytomylime.com" src="https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/How-to-Bake-Eggs-Pin-4-512x1024.jpg" alt="Two images of eggs baked in a muffin tin." class="wp-image-1701" srcset="https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/How-to-Bake-Eggs-Pin-4-512x1024.jpg 512w, https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/How-to-Bake-Eggs-Pin-4-150x300.jpg 150w, https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/How-to-Bake-Eggs-Pin-4.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px"  loading="eager"/></a></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Why and How to Meal Prep Eggs:</strong></h2>



<p>Meal prep is kind of my favorite thing and learning how to bake eggs has been such a lifesaver.</p>



<p>I&#8217;m a bit of a procrastinator by nature. Thankfully, <strong>meal prepping helps me stay on track</strong> even when I don&#8217;t think about food until I&#8217;m so hungry I could eat anything. <script async data-uid="40ecc36df9" src="https://prodigious-architect-2932.ck.page/40ecc36df9/index.js"></script></p>



<p><strong>Breakfast has always been my weak point</strong> when it comes to staying healthy.</p>



<p>I used to run out the door and snack on whatever I had on hand.</p>



<p>Sometimes that was fruit, sometimes that was granola, sometimes it was something way less healthy.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><a href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/257831147404902089/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><img decoding="async" width="900" height="600" data-pin-nopin="nopin" data-pin-url="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/?tp_image_id=762" data-pin-title="How to Bake Eggs in a Muffin Tin in the Oven" data-pin-description="Easy eggs in muffin tin! Baked eggs are so simple and so delicious. These baked eggs in a muffin tin make an awesome breakfast meal prep! #eggs #breakfastrecipes #breakfastmealprep #eggrecipes #bakedeggs #lowcarbbreakfast #ketobreakfast | keytomylime.com" src="https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Baked-Eggs-in-Muffin-Tin-3.jpg" alt="Baked eggs in a muffin tin." class="wp-image-762" srcset="https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Baked-Eggs-in-Muffin-Tin-3.jpg 900w, https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Baked-Eggs-in-Muffin-Tin-3-300x200.jpg 300w, https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Baked-Eggs-in-Muffin-Tin-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Baked-Eggs-in-Muffin-Tin-3-735x490.jpg 735w" sizes="auto"  loading="lazy" fetchpriority="low"/></a></figure>



<p>This definitely needed to change, because <strong>how I start my day influences my entire day</strong>.</p>



<p>I&#8217;m loving these oven baked eggs because I have such <strong>a better day when I start my day with protein</strong>.</p>



<p>I&#8217;ve tried meal prepping with hard boiled eggs, but I&#8217;m just not a fan. All the peeling just isn&#8217;t for me.</p>



<p>These easy baked eggs are the best because</p>



<ol class="wp-block-list"><li> <strong>They taste better than hard boiled eggs</strong><em>.</em></li><li> <strong>There&#8217;s no peeling involved!</strong></li></ol>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><a href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/257831147404902089/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><img decoding="async" width="600" height="900" data-pin-url="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/?tp_image_id=358" data-pin-title="How to Bake Eggs in a Muffin Tin in the Oven" data-pin-description="Easy eggs in muffin tin! Baked eggs are so simple and so delicious. These baked eggs in a muffin tin make an awesome breakfast meal prep! #eggs #breakfastrecipes #breakfastmealprep #eggrecipes #bakedeggs #lowcarbbreakfast #ketobreakfast | keytomylime.com" src="https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Raw-Eggs-in-Muffin-Tin.jpg" alt="Raw eggs in a muffin pan." class="wp-image-358" srcset="https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Raw-Eggs-in-Muffin-Tin.jpg 600w, https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Raw-Eggs-in-Muffin-Tin-200x300.jpg 200w" sizes="auto"  loading="lazy" fetchpriority="low"/></a></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>How to Bake Eggs in the Oven:</strong></h2>



<p>This <strong>baked eggs recipe</strong> is really just about the easiest recipe <em>ever</em>.</p>



<p>All you have to do is preheat the oven to 350 F, lightly grease a <strong><em><a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" aria-label="non-stick muffin pan (opens in a new tab)" href="https://amzn.to/34InyPG" target="_blank">non-stick muffin pan</a></em></strong> (I prefer using <strong><em><a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" aria-label="this spray oil (opens in a new tab)" href="https://amzn.to/2rlIM7x" target="_blank">this spray oil</a></em></strong>), crack your eggs into each muffin slot, and season them with salt and pepper to taste.</p>



<p>Bake them to your desired doneness, and store them in the fridge <strong><em><a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" aria-label="in an airtight container (opens in a new tab)" href="https://amzn.to/2pEAZkg" target="_blank">in an airtight container</a></em></strong> until you&#8217;re ready to eat them.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><a href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/257831147404902089/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><img loading="lazy" loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="600" height="900" data-pin-url="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/?tp_image_id=361" data-pin-title="How to Bake Eggs in a Muffin Tin in the Oven" data-pin-description="Easy eggs in muffin tin! Baked eggs are so simple and so delicious. These baked eggs in a muffin tin make an awesome breakfast meal prep! #eggs #breakfastrecipes #breakfastmealprep #eggrecipes #bakedeggs #lowcarbbreakfast #ketobreakfast | keytomylime.com" src="https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Baked-Eggs-in-Muffin-Tin-2.jpg" alt="Baked eggs in a muffin tin." class="wp-image-361" srcset="https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Baked-Eggs-in-Muffin-Tin-2.jpg 600w, https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Baked-Eggs-in-Muffin-Tin-2-200x300.jpg 200w" sizes="auto"  fetchpriority="low"/></a></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>How Long Does it Take to Bake Eggs in the Oven?</strong></h2>



<p>I bake my eggs at 350 F, and it takes anywhere from 14-17 minutes to bake them.</p>



<p>I prefer them baked for 14 minutes because the egg white is set and the egg yolk is still just a little jammy.</p>



<p>If you prefer your yolks more set, you could bake them for up to 17 minutes.</p>



<p>Just as a reference, the eggs in these photos were baked for 14 minutes.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><a href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/257831147404902089/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><img loading="lazy" loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="600" height="900" data-pin-url="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/?tp_image_id=362" data-pin-title="How to Bake Eggs in a Muffin Tin in the Oven" data-pin-description="Easy eggs in muffin tin! Baked eggs are so simple and so delicious. These baked eggs in a muffin tin make an awesome breakfast meal prep! #eggs #breakfastrecipes #breakfastmealprep #eggrecipes #bakedeggs #lowcarbbreakfast #ketobreakfast | keytomylime.com" src="https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Baked-Eggs-in-Muffin-Tin.jpg" alt="Baked eggs in a muffin tin." class="wp-image-362" srcset="https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Baked-Eggs-in-Muffin-Tin.jpg 600w, https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Baked-Eggs-in-Muffin-Tin-200x300.jpg 200w" sizes="auto"  fetchpriority="low"/></a></figure>



<p>If you&#8217;re excited to try baking eggs, you may love my <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Everything Bagel Cloud Eggs (opens in a new tab)" href="https://keytomylime.com/everything-bagel-cloud-eggs/" target="_blank"><strong>Everything Bagel Cloud Eggs</strong></a> recipe and my tutorial showing you how to <strong><a href="https://keytomylime.com/sheet-pan-eggs/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Fry Eggs in the Oven</a></strong>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><a href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/257831147404985277/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><img loading="lazy" loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="600" height="900" data-pin-url="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/?tp_image_id=359" data-pin-title="How to Bake Eggs in a Muffin Tin in the Oven" data-pin-description="Baked eggs in muffin tins are the easiest healthy breakfast meal prep! Not only was it easier than hard boiling eggs, it tasted so much better, too! #eggs #eggrecipes #bakedeggs #breakfastmealprep | keytomylime.com" src="https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Hand-Holding-Baked-Egg.jpg" alt="Hand holding an egg baked in a muffin tin." class="wp-image-359" srcset="https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Hand-Holding-Baked-Egg.jpg 600w, https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Hand-Holding-Baked-Egg-200x300.jpg 200w" sizes="auto"  fetchpriority="low"/></a></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>What you&#8217;ll need:</strong></h2>



<p>The beauty of this recipe is that you don&#8217;t need much to make it. You&#8217;ll need 1 tool and 1 ingredient (other than eggs) to get perfectly baked eggs.</p>



<p>The tool you&#8217;ll need is a good nonstick muffin pan. I like to cook things in smaller batches, so <strong><em><a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" aria-label="I normally use this muffin pan (opens in a new tab)" href="https://amzn.to/2Q2Wl64" target="_blank">I normally use this muffin pan</a></em></strong>. If you&#8217;re cooking for lots of people, try this <em><strong><a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" aria-label="durable nonstick muffin tin (opens in a new tab)" href="https://amzn.to/34InyPG" target="_blank">durable nonstick muffin tin</a></strong></em>.</p>



<p>The ingredient you&#8217;ll need is oil or butter to grease the pan. <strong><em><a href="https://amzn.to/2rlIM7x" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" aria-label="I like using spray oil, and this is my favorite one. (opens in a new tab)">I like using spray oil, and this is my favorite one.</a></em></strong> I love that it&#8217;s Propellant-Free, Non-GMO, and still affordable.</p>


