</div>
	<div class="mv-create-ingredients">
		<h2 class="mv-create-ingredients-title mv-create-title-secondary">Ingredients</h2>

											<ul>
									<li>
						12 eggs					</li>
									<li>
						Oil or butter to grease the pan					</li>
									<li>
						Salt to taste					</li>
									<li>
						Pepper to taste					</li>
							</ul>
			</div>
		<div class="mv-create-hands-free"></div>
		<div class="mv-create-instructions mv-create-instructions-slot-v2">
		<h2 class="mv-create-instructions-title mv-create-title-secondary">Instructions</h2>
		<ol><li id="mv_create_13_1">Preheat oven to 350 F.</li><li id="mv_create_13_2">Lightly grease the <a href="https://amzn.to/34InyPG" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">non-stick muffin pan</a> with oil, butter, or <a href="https://amzn.to/2rlIM7x" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">spray oil</a>.</li><li id="mv_create_13_3">Crack each egg into one of the muffin openings.</li><li id="mv_create_13_4">Season with salt and pepper to taste.</li><li id="mv_create_13_5">Bake for 14-17 minutes, or until the whites don’t jiggle and the yolks reach your desired level of doneness (the ones in the photo were baked for 14 minutes).</li></ol>	</div>
	<div class="mv-create-notes mv-create-notes-slot-v2">
		<h2 class="mv-create-notes-title mv-create-title-secondary">Notes</h2>
		<div class="mv-create-notes-content">
			<p><p>This recipe can be easily halved if you’re working with <a href="https://amzn.to/2Q2Wl64" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">a smaller muffin pan</a>.</p></p>
		</div>
	</div>
<div class="mv-create-nutrition">
