<p>Let me know what you think of this recipe in the comments and on Instagram <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="@keytomylime (opens in a new tab)" href="https://www.instagram.com/keytomylime/" target="_blank">@keytomylime</a> #keytomylime and <a href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/257831147404902089/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="pin this recipe for later (opens in a new tab)">pin this recipe for later</a>!</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><a href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/257831147404929511/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><img loading="lazy" loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="512" height="1024" data-pin-nopin="nopin" data-pin-url="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/?tp_image_id=455" data-pin-title="How to Bake Eggs in a Muffin Tin in the Oven" data-pin-id="257831147404929511" data-pin-description="Baked eggs in muffin tins are so delicious! They're the perfect way to meal prep for breakfast and they taste so much better than hard boiled eggs! #mealprep #breakfastmealprep #bakedeggs #eggs | keytomylime.com" src="https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/How-to-Bake-Eggs-Pin-2-512x1024.jpg" alt="Two images showing how to bake eggs in a muffin tin in the oven." class="wp-image-455" srcset="https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/How-to-Bake-Eggs-Pin-2-512x1024.jpg 512w, https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/How-to-Bake-Eggs-Pin-2-150x300.jpg 150w, https://keytomylime.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/How-to-Bake-Eggs-Pin-2.jpg 600w" sizes="auto"  fetchpriority="low"/></a></figure>



<p>Are you looking for more breakfast meal prep recipes? <a href="https://www.ambitiouskitchen.com/16-healthy-breakfast-recipes-perfect-meal-prep/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Ambitious Kitchen (opens in a new tab)">Ambitious Kitchen</a> has some amazing healthy breakfast meal prep recipes on her site.</p>



<p>Now that you know <strong>how to bake eggs</strong>, I hope you&#8217;ll give this easy breakfast meal prep a try!</p>
