									</footer>

				<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>Hi Sally, This would work great with scrambled eggs, too! -Alexa</p>
<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-5561' data-commentid="5561" data-postid="363" data-belowelement="div-comment-5561" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Alexa Blay" aria-label='Reply to Alexa Blay'>Reply</a></span>				</div>
			</article>
			</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->

		<li id="comment-4701" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent">
			<article class="comment-body" id="div-comment-4701"  itemtype="https://schema.org/Comment" itemscope>
				<footer class="comment-meta" aria-label="Comment meta">
										<div class="comment-author-info">
						<div class="comment-author vcard" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" itemscope>
							<cite itemprop="name" class="fn">Scott</cite>						</div>

													<div class="entry-meta comment-metadata">
								<a href="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/#comment-4701">									<time datetime="2021-08-22T10:49:19-04:00" itemprop="datePublished">
										August 22, 2021 at 10:49 am									</time>
								</a>							</div>
												</div>

									</footer>

				<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>My oven it takes about 12 mins.I added garlic and onion powder and bacon bits.Love the recipe I make every other day at night so the kids have for breakfast before school!</p>
<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-4701' data-commentid="4701" data-postid="363" data-belowelement="div-comment-4701" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Scott" aria-label='Reply to Scott'>Reply</a></span>				</div>
			</article>
			<ul class="children">

		<li id="comment-4767" class="comment byuser comment-author-lexyblay bypostauthor odd alt depth-2">
			<article class="comment-body" id="div-comment-4767"  itemtype="https://schema.org/Comment" itemscope>
				<footer class="comment-meta" aria-label="Comment meta">
										<div class="comment-author-info">
						<div class="comment-author vcard" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" itemscope>
							<cite itemprop="name" class="fn">Alexa Blay</cite>						</div>

													<div class="entry-meta comment-metadata">
								<a href="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/#comment-4767">									<time datetime="2021-08-26T20:10:43-04:00" itemprop="datePublished">
										August 26, 2021 at 8:10 pm									</time>
								</a>							</div>
												</div>

									</footer>

				<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>So happy to hear you enjoy making this recipe so often, Scott! Thanks so much for the feedback about the cooking time that works for your oven. Those flavor add-ins sound delicious, too! -Alexa</p>
<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-4767' data-commentid="4767" data-postid="363" data-belowelement="div-comment-4767" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Alexa Blay" aria-label='Reply to Alexa Blay'>Reply</a></span>				</div>
			</article>
			</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->

		<li id="comment-4808" class="comment even thread-even depth-1 parent">
			<article class="comment-body" id="div-comment-4808"  itemtype="https://schema.org/Comment" itemscope>
				<footer class="comment-meta" aria-label="Comment meta">
										<div class="comment-author-info">
						<div class="comment-author vcard" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" itemscope>
							<cite itemprop="name" class="fn">Jennifer</cite>						</div>

													<div class="entry-meta comment-metadata">
								<a href="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/#comment-4808">									<time datetime="2021-08-30T18:14:16-04:00" itemprop="datePublished">
										August 30, 2021 at 6:14 pm									</time>
								</a>							</div>
												</div>

									</footer>

				<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>Any suggestions for reheating the stores eggs?</p>
<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-4808' data-commentid="4808" data-postid="363" data-belowelement="div-comment-4808" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Jennifer" aria-label='Reply to Jennifer'>Reply</a></span>				</div>
			</article>
			<ul class="children">

		<li id="comment-4894" class="comment byuser comment-author-lexyblay bypostauthor odd alt depth-2 parent">
			<article class="comment-body" id="div-comment-4894"  itemtype="https://schema.org/Comment" itemscope>
				<footer class="comment-meta" aria-label="Comment meta">
										<div class="comment-author-info">
						<div class="comment-author vcard" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" itemscope>
							<cite itemprop="name" class="fn">Alexa Blay</cite>						</div>

													<div class="entry-meta comment-metadata">
								<a href="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/#comment-4894">									<time datetime="2021-09-04T07:37:31-04:00" itemprop="datePublished">
										September 4, 2021 at 7:37 am									</time>
								</a>							</div>
												</div>

									</footer>

				<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>Hi Jennifer, The easiest way to reheat fried eggs would be in either the microwave on the stove. In the microwave trying wrapping it in a paper towel and microwaving it for 15 seconds, then flip it and heat for another 15 seconds. Continue doing this until the egg is as hot as you like it. On the stove, add a bit of water or butter to a skillet over medium heat, then add the egg and heat until it&#8217;s warmed through (about 2 minutes). Hope that helps! -Alexa</p>
<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-4894' data-commentid="4894" data-postid="363" data-belowelement="div-comment-4894" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Alexa Blay" aria-label='Reply to Alexa Blay'>Reply</a></span>				</div>
			</article>
			<ul class="children">

		<li id="comment-11931" class="comment even depth-3">
			<article class="comment-body" id="div-comment-11931"  itemtype="https://schema.org/Comment" itemscope>
				<footer class="comment-meta" aria-label="Comment meta">
										<div class="comment-author-info">
						<div class="comment-author vcard" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" itemscope>
							<cite itemprop="name" class="fn">Beth</cite>						</div>

													<div class="entry-meta comment-metadata">
								<a href="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/#comment-11931">									<time datetime="2022-09-17T07:41:45-04:00" itemprop="datePublished">
										September 17, 2022 at 7:41 am									</time>
								</a>							</div>
												</div>

									</footer>

				<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>I would suggest heatin in the microwave at 50% for 30 seconds so it doesn’t cook more, just heat</p>
<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-11931' data-commentid="11931" data-postid="363" data-belowelement="div-comment-11931" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Beth" aria-label='Reply to Beth'>Reply</a></span>				</div>
			</article>
			</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->

		<li id="comment-5084" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent">
			<article class="comment-body" id="div-comment-5084"  itemtype="https://schema.org/Comment" itemscope>
				<footer class="comment-meta" aria-label="Comment meta">
										<div class="comment-author-info">
						<div class="comment-author vcard" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" itemscope>
							<cite itemprop="name" class="fn">Jack Catanzarite</cite>						</div>

													<div class="entry-meta comment-metadata">
								<a href="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/#comment-5084">									<time datetime="2021-09-20T06:25:11-04:00" itemprop="datePublished">
										September 20, 2021 at 6:25 am									</time>
								</a>							</div>
												</div>

									</footer>

				<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>Great way to make eggs &amp; they taste great!  I used butter to grease the pan &amp; sprinkled Parmesan cheese on top of the eggs too for a twist. Thanks!</p>
<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-5084' data-commentid="5084" data-postid="363" data-belowelement="div-comment-5084" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Jack Catanzarite" aria-label='Reply to Jack Catanzarite'>Reply</a></span>				</div>
			</article>
			<ul class="children">

		<li id="comment-5110" class="comment byuser comment-author-lexyblay bypostauthor even depth-2 parent">
			<article class="comment-body" id="div-comment-5110"  itemtype="https://schema.org/Comment" itemscope>
				<footer class="comment-meta" aria-label="Comment meta">
										<div class="comment-author-info">
						<div class="comment-author vcard" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" itemscope>
							<cite itemprop="name" class="fn">Alexa Blay</cite>						</div>

													<div class="entry-meta comment-metadata">
								<a href="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/#comment-5110">									<time datetime="2021-09-22T16:17:05-04:00" itemprop="datePublished">
										September 22, 2021 at 4:17 pm									</time>
								</a>							</div>
												</div>

									</footer>

				<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>So happy you like the baked eggs, Jack! I love adding parmesan to them, too &#8211; such a great addition! -Alexa</p>
<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-5110' data-commentid="5110" data-postid="363" data-belowelement="div-comment-5110" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Alexa Blay" aria-label='Reply to Alexa Blay'>Reply</a></span>				</div>
			</article>
			<ul class="children">

		<li id="comment-5386" class="comment odd alt depth-3">
			<article class="comment-body" id="div-comment-5386"  itemtype="https://schema.org/Comment" itemscope>
				<footer class="comment-meta" aria-label="Comment meta">
										<div class="comment-author-info">
						<div class="comment-author vcard" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" itemscope>
							<cite itemprop="name" class="fn">Talluha</cite>						</div>

													<div class="entry-meta comment-metadata">
								<a href="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/#comment-5386">									<time datetime="2021-10-10T21:14:23-04:00" itemprop="datePublished">
										October 10, 2021 at 9:14 pm									</time>
								</a>							</div>
												</div>

									</footer>

				<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>Back in the 1950’s our family had baked eggs once a week. My father would use the muffin tins but he would line them with the muffin cup paper. This was a night meal along with broccoli and homemade Hollandaise Sauce.  Then the eggs were topped with chip beef and lots of black pepper along with shredded cheese.  I haven’t  eaten baked eggs in 60 years.  I’ll try your recipe and but will use muffin tin paper liners for less cleanup.  Hummy!</p>
<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-5386' data-commentid="5386" data-postid="363" data-belowelement="div-comment-5386" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Talluha" aria-label='Reply to Talluha'>Reply</a></span>				</div>
			</article>
			</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->

		<li id="comment-6626" class="comment even thread-even depth-1 parent">
			<article class="comment-body" id="div-comment-6626"  itemtype="https://schema.org/Comment" itemscope>
				<footer class="comment-meta" aria-label="Comment meta">
										<div class="comment-author-info">
						<div class="comment-author vcard" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" itemscope>
							<cite itemprop="name" class="fn">Dotti</cite>						</div>

													<div class="entry-meta comment-metadata">
								<a href="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/#comment-6626">									<time datetime="2021-12-19T15:14:03-04:00" itemprop="datePublished">
										December 19, 2021 at 3:14 pm									</time>
								</a>							</div>
												</div>

									</footer>

				<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>Tried the Baked Eggs;  LOVED them.  Will be having these alot.</p>
<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-6626' data-commentid="6626" data-postid="363" data-belowelement="div-comment-6626" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Dotti" aria-label='Reply to Dotti'>Reply</a></span>				</div>
			</article>
			<ul class="children">

		<li id="comment-6641" class="comment byuser comment-author-lexyblay bypostauthor odd alt depth-2">
			<article class="comment-body" id="div-comment-6641"  itemtype="https://schema.org/Comment" itemscope>
				<footer class="comment-meta" aria-label="Comment meta">
										<div class="comment-author-info">
						<div class="comment-author vcard" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" itemscope>
							<cite itemprop="name" class="fn">Alexa Blay</cite>						</div>

													<div class="entry-meta comment-metadata">
								<a href="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/#comment-6641">									<time datetime="2021-12-20T06:45:28-04:00" itemprop="datePublished">
										December 20, 2021 at 6:45 am									</time>
								</a>							</div>
												</div>

									</footer>

				<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>Hi Dotti, So happy to hear you loved the baked eggs! Thanks so much for leaving feedback. -Alexa</p>
<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-6641' data-commentid="6641" data-postid="363" data-belowelement="div-comment-6641" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Alexa Blay" aria-label='Reply to Alexa Blay'>Reply</a></span>				</div>
			</article>
			</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->

		<li id="comment-7959" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent">
			<article class="comment-body" id="div-comment-7959"  itemtype="https://schema.org/Comment" itemscope>
				<footer class="comment-meta" aria-label="Comment meta">
										<div class="comment-author-info">
						<div class="comment-author vcard" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" itemscope>
							<cite itemprop="name" class="fn">Tara Smith</cite>						</div>

													<div class="entry-meta comment-metadata">
								<a href="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/#comment-7959">									<time datetime="2022-03-10T22:35:09-04:00" itemprop="datePublished">
										March 10, 2022 at 10:35 pm									</time>
								</a>							</div>
												</div>

									</footer>

				<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>Question.  Can they be warmed in a microwave?</p>
<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-7959' data-commentid="7959" data-postid="363" data-belowelement="div-comment-7959" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Tara Smith" aria-label='Reply to Tara Smith'>Reply</a></span>				</div>
			</article>
			<ul class="children">

		<li id="comment-7968" class="comment byuser comment-author-lexyblay bypostauthor odd alt depth-2">
			<article class="comment-body" id="div-comment-7968"  itemtype="https://schema.org/Comment" itemscope>
				<footer class="comment-meta" aria-label="Comment meta">
										<div class="comment-author-info">
						<div class="comment-author vcard" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" itemscope>
							<cite itemprop="name" class="fn">Alexa Blay</cite>						</div>

													<div class="entry-meta comment-metadata">
								<a href="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/#comment-7968">									<time datetime="2022-03-11T07:21:09-04:00" itemprop="datePublished">
										March 11, 2022 at 7:21 am									</time>
								</a>							</div>
												</div>

									</footer>

				<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>Hi Tara, Yes, they can. In the microwave try sprinkling it with a little bit of water then wrapping it in a paper towel and microwaving it for 15 seconds, then flip it and heat for another 15 seconds. Continue doing this until the egg is as hot as you like it (minimum 165F internal, but it can quickly get hotter than that in the microwave). Hope that helps! -Alexa</p>
<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-7968' data-commentid="7968" data-postid="363" data-belowelement="div-comment-7968" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Alexa Blay" aria-label='Reply to Alexa Blay'>Reply</a></span>				</div>
			</article>
			</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->

		<li id="comment-8455" class="comment even thread-even depth-1 parent">
			<article class="comment-body" id="div-comment-8455"  itemtype="https://schema.org/Comment" itemscope>
				<footer class="comment-meta" aria-label="Comment meta">
										<div class="comment-author-info">
						<div class="comment-author vcard" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" itemscope>
							<cite itemprop="name" class="fn">Laurie</cite>						</div>

													<div class="entry-meta comment-metadata">
								<a href="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/#comment-8455">									<time datetime="2022-04-10T22:44:20-04:00" itemprop="datePublished">
										April 10, 2022 at 10:44 pm									</time>
								</a>							</div>
												</div>

									</footer>

				<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>Hi I was wanting to freeze them. Any advice on how, for how long and best way to reheat?</p>
<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-8455' data-commentid="8455" data-postid="363" data-belowelement="div-comment-8455" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Laurie" aria-label='Reply to Laurie'>Reply</a></span>				</div>
			</article>
			<ul class="children">

		<li id="comment-9045" class="comment byuser comment-author-lexyblay bypostauthor odd alt depth-2">
			<article class="comment-body" id="div-comment-9045"  itemtype="https://schema.org/Comment" itemscope>
				<footer class="comment-meta" aria-label="Comment meta">
										<div class="comment-author-info">
						<div class="comment-author vcard" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" itemscope>
							<cite itemprop="name" class="fn">Alexa Blay</cite>						</div>

													<div class="entry-meta comment-metadata">
								<a href="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/#comment-9045">									<time datetime="2022-05-07T20:57:44-04:00" itemprop="datePublished">
										May 7, 2022 at 8:57 pm									</time>
								</a>							</div>
												</div>

									</footer>

				<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>Hi Laurie, I&#8217;d arrange them on a baking sheet, then freeze them for 1-2 hours before transferring them to an airtight container to store in the freezer for up to 2 months. I haven&#8217;t tested it, but I think the best way to reheat them would be in a microwave. -Alexa</p>
<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-9045' data-commentid="9045" data-postid="363" data-belowelement="div-comment-9045" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Alexa Blay" aria-label='Reply to Alexa Blay'>Reply</a></span>				</div>
			</article>
			</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->

		<li id="comment-8536" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent">
			<article class="comment-body" id="div-comment-8536"  itemtype="https://schema.org/Comment" itemscope>
				<footer class="comment-meta" aria-label="Comment meta">
										<div class="comment-author-info">
						<div class="comment-author vcard" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" itemscope>
							<cite itemprop="name" class="fn">Yvonne</cite>						</div>

													<div class="entry-meta comment-metadata">
								<a href="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/#comment-8536">									<time datetime="2022-04-15T15:28:10-04:00" itemprop="datePublished">
										April 15, 2022 at 3:28 pm									</time>
								</a>							</div>
												</div>

									</footer>

				<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>I saw the comment about baking scramble eggs. How would you do that?</p>
<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-8536' data-commentid="8536" data-postid="363" data-belowelement="div-comment-8536" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Yvonne" aria-label='Reply to Yvonne'>Reply</a></span>				</div>
			</article>
			<ul class="children">

		<li id="comment-8638" class="comment byuser comment-author-lexyblay bypostauthor odd alt depth-2 parent">
			<article class="comment-body" id="div-comment-8638"  itemtype="https://schema.org/Comment" itemscope>
				<footer class="comment-meta" aria-label="Comment meta">
										<div class="comment-author-info">
						<div class="comment-author vcard" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" itemscope>
							<cite itemprop="name" class="fn">Alexa Blay</cite>						</div>

													<div class="entry-meta comment-metadata">
								<a href="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/#comment-8638">									<time datetime="2022-04-20T08:53:34-04:00" itemprop="datePublished">
										April 20, 2022 at 8:53 am									</time>
								</a>							</div>
												</div>

									</footer>

				<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>Hi Yvonne, You could whisk together eggs, seasonings, milk, etc. in a bowl, then evenly pour the mixture into a greased muffin tin and bake according to the recipe instructions. -Alexa</p>
<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-8638' data-commentid="8638" data-postid="363" data-belowelement="div-comment-8638" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Alexa Blay" aria-label='Reply to Alexa Blay'>Reply</a></span>				</div>
			</article>
			<ul class="children">

		<li id="comment-51319" class="comment even depth-3">
			<article class="comment-body" id="div-comment-51319"  itemtype="https://schema.org/Comment" itemscope>
				<footer class="comment-meta" aria-label="Comment meta">
										<div class="comment-author-info">
						<div class="comment-author vcard" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" itemscope>
							<cite itemprop="name" class="fn">Heather Burch</cite>						</div>

													<div class="entry-meta comment-metadata">
								<a href="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/#comment-51319">									<time datetime="2025-05-18T07:27:34-04:00" itemprop="datePublished">
										May 18, 2025 at 7:27 am									</time>
								</a>							</div>
												</div>

									</footer>

				<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>Made 3 pans of these for a large  gathering for breakfast sandwiches and they came out great! Just make sure to grease your pan well so they don’t stick! Thanks Alexa!</p>
<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-51319' data-commentid="51319" data-postid="363" data-belowelement="div-comment-51319" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Heather Burch" aria-label='Reply to Heather Burch'>Reply</a></span>				</div>
			</article>
			</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->

		<li id="comment-13207" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1">
			<article class="comment-body" id="div-comment-13207"  itemtype="https://schema.org/Comment" itemscope>
				<footer class="comment-meta" aria-label="Comment meta">
										<div class="comment-author-info">
						<div class="comment-author vcard" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" itemscope>
							<cite itemprop="name" class="fn">Barb</cite>						</div>

													<div class="entry-meta comment-metadata">
								<a href="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/#comment-13207">									<time datetime="2022-11-20T21:12:08-04:00" itemprop="datePublished">
										November 20, 2022 at 9:12 pm									</time>
								</a>							</div>
												</div>

									</footer>

				<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>Late to the party here, but just want to add for folks wondering about reheating options. I had baked eggs for years then stopped. Stumbled upon this recipe as I was looking for temp/time again since it has been so long&#8230; they turned out great!  What I do is assemble a freshly toasted english muffin with a little butter, one of these eggs (from the fridge!) cheese and a thin slice of ham then wrap in parchment paper. Microwave for 45 seconds and you have the best breaky ever! Thanks for this post!</p>
<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-13207' data-commentid="13207" data-postid="363" data-belowelement="div-comment-13207" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Barb" aria-label='Reply to Barb'>Reply</a></span>				</div>
			</article>
			</li><!-- #comment-## -->

		<li id="comment-15491" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
			<article class="comment-body" id="div-comment-15491"  itemtype="https://schema.org/Comment" itemscope>
				<footer class="comment-meta" aria-label="Comment meta">
										<div class="comment-author-info">
						<div class="comment-author vcard" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" itemscope>
							<cite itemprop="name" class="fn">MrsRobo</cite>						</div>

													<div class="entry-meta comment-metadata">
								<a href="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/#comment-15491">									<time datetime="2023-02-18T15:53:33-04:00" itemprop="datePublished">
										February 18, 2023 at 3:53 pm									</time>
								</a>							</div>
												</div>

									</footer>

				<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>I don&#8217;t like yolk at all. I like hard fried eggs. Has anyone made this by whisking the eggs a bit before baking to make it more blended? I&#8217;m guessing it would work. Thanks</p>
<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-15491' data-commentid="15491" data-postid="363" data-belowelement="div-comment-15491" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to MrsRobo" aria-label='Reply to MrsRobo'>Reply</a></span>				</div>
			</article>
			</li><!-- #comment-## -->

		<li id="comment-61304" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1">
			<article class="comment-body" id="div-comment-61304"  itemtype="https://schema.org/Comment" itemscope>
				<footer class="comment-meta" aria-label="Comment meta">
										<div class="comment-author-info">
						<div class="comment-author vcard" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" itemscope>
							<cite itemprop="name" class="fn">Amanda</cite>						</div>

													<div class="entry-meta comment-metadata">
								<a href="https://keytomylime.com/how-to-bake-eggs/#comment-61304">									<time datetime="2025-08-17T13:15:08-04:00" itemprop="datePublished">
										August 17, 2025 at 1:15 pm									</time>
								</a>							</div>
												</div>

									</footer>

				<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>Hi, I’ve only made this recipe once and it was delicious at 14 mins bake time like you recommended for jammy eggs. How long do I store them in the fridge in an air tight container? Thank you!</p>
<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-61304' data-commentid="61304" data-postid="363" data-belowelement="div-comment-61304" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Amanda" aria-label='Reply to Amanda'>Reply</a></span>				</div>
			</article>
			</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		</ol><!-- .comment-list -->

			<div id="respond" class="comment-respond">
		<h3 id="reply-title" class="comment-reply-title">Leave a Comment <small><a rel="nofollow" id="cancel-comment-reply-link" href="/how-to-bake-eggs/#respond" style="display:none;">Cancel reply</a></small></h3><form action="https://keytomylime.com/wp-comments-post.php" method="post" id="commentform" class="comment-form" novalidate><div class="comment-form-wprm-rating" style="display: none">
